_:f673ed3383b3fa1c23dee77fcbb84f3 a <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E52_Time-span> ;
	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> " He was a prominent 17th century nobleman and high ranking officer \n                  of \n                  \n                     ʾaṣe Susǝnyos. \n                  He was the husband of \n                  \n                     ʾƎmmat Walatta Ṗeṭros from whom he had three children. \n                  He was very loyal to  \n                  \n                     ʾaṣe Susǝnyos despite the king's  inclination to Catholicism. He was\n                  involved in many anti-Catholic rebels assisting the king  but\n                  in the final years of \n                  \n                     ʾaṣe Susǝnyos, \n                  Malkǝʾa Krǝstos was in tension with the king and in 1632  he avoided campaigning against the rebels. \n                  Finally, he was arrested, accused of treason and sentenced to death which was substituted by exile." .
<https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6609Malkea> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P4_has_time_span> _:f673ed3383b3fa1c23dee77fcbb84f3 ;
